Major crash on M7 Durban, claims one life, two serious with multiple others injured. DURBAN - One person has been killed and approximately 15 others injured in a horrific accident on the M7 Durban Bound before Bellville Offramp on Wednesday morning. The accident which happened around 8am, involved six cars and three trucks. READ: Two injured after light aircraft crashes in Springs According to Rescue Care Paramedics, three vehicles involved in the collision caught alight after impact. "Multiple patients were found on both carriageways of the freeway as people fled the scene due to the fire," Rescue Care Paramedics said. "Immediately more ambulances, as well as Advanced Life Support Paramedics, were dispatched to the scene. Durban Fire Department was also dispatched to assist."